-- UK opens books on sale of 2068 conventional gilt
-- By Andy Bruce
-- Tue Oct 28, 2014 04:47AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Oct 28 (Reuters) - Britain opened the books on the syndication of its longest-dated conventional gilt, which matures in 2068, one of the bookrunners on the transaction said on Tuesday.

Investors are being offered the July 2068 bond  <GBT3H68=> at a spread ranging from 2.5 basis points to 3 basis points above the 2060 gilt.